# Phase 4: Meta-Cognition + Contextual Awareness Architecture

## System Overview

Phase 4 introduces three new cognitive layers that enable AZME to think about its own thinking, adapt to context, and schedule its activities temporally.

## Architecture Diagram

```mermaid
graph TD
    %% Core Cognitive Layers
    A[ExecutionTrace] --> B[MetaCognitionEngine]
    B --> C[ContextEngine]
    C --> D[TemporalScheduler]
    
    %% Meta-Cognition Flow
    B -->|Evaluate| E[GlobalState]
    E -->|Trigger| F[MetaThought]
    F -->|Action| G[Reroute/Mutate]
    G -->|Update| H[ThoughtQueue]
    
    %% Contextual Awareness Flow
    C -->|Filter| I[Thought Selection]
    I -->|Prefer Tags| J[ContextBlock]
    J -->|Adjust Priority| K[ThoughtQueue]
    
    %% Temporal Reasoning Flow
    D -->|Schedule| L[Periodic Tasks]
    L -->|Tick| M[Time Simulation]
    M -->|Execute| N[Scheduled Thoughts]
    
    %% Integration Points
    H --> O[ReflectionEngine]
    K --> O
    N --> O
    
    %% Agent Scope
    P[AgentScope] --> Q[Agent-Specific Thoughts]
    Q --> R[Multi-Agent Coordination]
    
    %% Meta-Reflection Loop
    O -->|Score| S[ScoreVector]
    S -->|Update| E
    E -->|Trigger| F
    
    %% Styling
    classDef metaLayer fill:#ff9999,stroke:#333,stroke-width:2px
